<HL> Financing Business:
Giant Yellowknife Mines Ltd.</HL>
<DD> 10/09/87</DD>
<SO> WALL STREET JOURNAL (J)</SO>
<IN> GYK T.PAM </IN>
<TEXT>
   GIANT YELLOWKNIFE MINES LTD. in Toronto said it placed 1.4 million shares of common stock with Giant Resources Ltd. in Australia at 28.25 Canadian dollars ($21.63) each, for a total of 39.5 million Canadian dollars ($30.3 million). 
Giant Yellowknife closed at 33.75 dollars, up 50 cents, in Toronto Stock Exchange trading yesterday. 
Giant Yellowknife, a gold mining concern, is controlled by Ariadne Australia Ltd., a resource concern, through its 64%-owned Giant Resources and an affiliated company, Pamour Inc. 
The placement gives Giant Resources a 16.7% stake in Giant Yellowknife. 
The Canadian company said it also arranged a 60 million dollar credit facility with a banking syndicate, 50 million dollars of which is backed by Giant Yellowknife's expected gold production. 
Giant Yellowknife said funds drawn under the credit facility will be used for capital investment and to increase gold output. 

